<br>
Perhaps I have misjudged you, perhaps not; it does not matter anymore.  You are not a threat to me, I do not fear you; fear is for the weak, and though I have faced my share of weaknesses, you will find me greatly changed.<br>
<br>
Because you see, Merteuil... my prayers have finally been answered.  I have prayed to our Lord to fill my heart with hatred, to expel those sentiments unworthy of me, to root out all weakness... and it has finally come to pass.  In that moment, when Mlain and I were wed... that moment, when Mlain said &quot;Mekora, I hate you&quot; and I looked into his eyes and saw the depth and the purity of Innoruuk's hatred, something within me changed.  His is the example I must follow, which will lead me ever closer to serving our Father's will.<br>
<br>
I am dead inside, Merteuil, dead save for the fires of hate which burn within my heart.  No longer am I tormented by feelings which have no place in the heart of a true child of Innoruuk.  I feel nothing for Zenogias, for Daladdar, not even for you.  Mlain and I are one now and any who dare oppose us will fall before our might.<br>
<br>
As for Aeeny, she will die as will all paladins, but I have not singled her out.  Zenogias may do with her as he pleases, it is no concern of mine.  If he chooses her over his own people, then he will die as a traitor to our race, it is that simple.  Stykos will die as well; he seems to believe that we have achieved some sort of friendship, just because I did not fight him when I had the chance, but he will see in the end that he was wrong.<br>
<br>
Our reign of darkness has only just begun.<br>
<br>
